<text>NVE


A molecular simulation protocol that means to restrict the trajectory or sampling points on the hyper surface in the phase space which statisfies the condition that the number of atoms (N), volume (V) and total energy (E) are maintained constant. This protocol is always used to simulate completely isolated system and computationally generate microcanonical ensembles. Total energy is conserved only under NVE. If the Hamiltonian is time-symmetric (e.g. no friction), NVE is the default protocol implied in the Newtonian equations of motion. 


 
